==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[heahweg|hēahweġ]]'' ("main road"), corresponding to [[high]] + [[way]] (Old English ''[[heah|hēah]]'' ‘of great height, tall’ < Proto-Germanic ''*kaukhaz'' < Proto-Indo-European ''*koukos'' ‘hill’; + Old English [[weg#Old English|weġ]] ‘road, path’ < Proto-Germanic ''*wegaz'' < Proto-Indo-European base ''*wegh-'' ‘to move’).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈhaɪweɪ/}}
